questions.question_text:
Consider a dataset with eight observations located at {1.0, 1.2, 1.5, 2.0, 2.2, 2.5, 3.0, 3.2}. We will cluster the dataset using the k-means algorithm using k = 3 clusters and initialize the clusters at the locations of the first three observations, i.e. cluster 1 initially located at 1.0, cluster 2 at 1.2 and cluster 3 at 1.5. What will be the converged clustering of the eight observations using the k-means procedure based on Euclidean distance as dissimilarity?

A. {1.0}, {1.2, 1.5}, {2.0, 2.2, 2.5, 3.0, 3.2}
B. {1.0, 1.2}, {1.5}, {2.0, 2.2, 2.5, 3.0, 3.2}
C. {1.0, 1.2, 1.5}, {2.0, 2.2, 2.5}, {3.0, 3.2}
D. {1.0, 1.2, 1.5}, {2.0, 2.2}, {2.5, 3.0, 3.2}
